description:
&lt;p&gt;The Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust (MSEFT) is operating within a rapidly changing, challenging but very exciting time of whole system reformation. Over the next few years, through working together and in partnership with the other sites comprising MSEFT , they will define the future of care for the population of mid and south Essex.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of this acute trust collaboration we are redesigning our hospitals to ensure we meet rising demand with the best quality services. The Pharmacy Department is at the forefront of our service redesign and one of the first departments within the MSEFT to offer the opportunities for developing standardised systems across the three hospitals, re-designing new and on-going services as the clinical configuration changes in line with the Carter Report. This is all being led by a group chief pharmacist working in partnership across the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To fulfill Lord Carter’s requirement and to make our three local hospital pharmacy teams fit for the future, we have designed our Pharmacy Transformation Programme with the aim to provide the right intervention, at the right time and in the right place to ensure best outcomes and efficient use of resources.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a great opportunity for a highly motivated, open minded and dynamic Pharmacists to support the delivery of our clinical pharmacy service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This rotational post consists of 6 month rotations across a variety of specialist clinical areas including general medicine, surgery, women &amp; children and medication safety, as well as contribute to the provision of the &#39;on-call&#39; service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will therefore need to be an excellent communicator with strong interpersonal/ relationship building skills, have good service delivery senior management experience and a proven track record of leading and managing change within dynamic environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
